    "long_instructions": "# Lesson 7: Data Stories\r\n\r\n#### In this lesson, students will explore expository and persuasive data stories, examining real-life examples to understand what makes them engaging and insightful.\r\n\r\n___\r\n\r\n## Expository and Persuasive Data Stories\r\n\r\n#### Take a look at the examples from the lesson.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 20px; margin-top: 20px;\">\r\n\t<div style=\"background-color: #ffffff; box-shadow: 0px 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3); padding: 15px; border-radius: 10px; width: 45%;\">\r\n    <p style=\"color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><b>Expository Data Story</b></p>\r\n    <p style=\"color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><i>Tells a story about a person, place, thing, or event using data</i></p>\r\n\t<br>\r\n    <div style=\"display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;\">\r\n    \t<a href=\"https://studio.code.org/s/intro-to-data-science-2024/lessons/7/levels/1\" target=\"blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/47623db410174d08aeaea4da4648ef50-image-1733781085199.50.46â€¯PM.png\" alt=\"Three cards with images and corresponding text show a user their listening style. The titles are Vampire, Alchemist, and Time Traveler.\" style=\"width: 100%; margin-bottom: 10px;\"></a>\r\n\t</div>\r\n        <p style=\"color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 12px\">Click the image above to see a larger version.</p>\r\n\t\t<br>\r\n\t\t<p style=\"color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><b>Spotify Year Wrapped</b> cards tell the user how their listening habits throughout the year are unique.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\t<div style=\"background-color: #ffffff; box-shadow: 0px 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3); padding: 15px; border-radius: 10px; width: 45%;\">\r\n\t<p style=\"color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><b>Persuasive Data Story</b></p>\r\n    <p style=\"color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><i>Attempts to convince the audience of a stance based on evidence from data and visualizations</i></p>\r\n    <br>\r\n\t<div style=\"display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;\">   \r\n\t\t<a href=\"https://studio.code.org/s/intro-to-data-science-2024/lessons/7/levels/2\" target=\"blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://images.code.org/84dae9bcc77482c22ab70dce932715e4-image-1733781085193.51.04â€¯PM.png\" alt=\"An infographic demonstrates Lebron James' basketball achievements.\" style=\"width: 100%;  margin-bottom: 10px;\"></a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \t<p style=\"color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 12px\">Click the image above to see a larger version.</p>\r\n\t\t<br>\r\n        <p style=\"color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\">This <b>Lebron James</b> infographic aims to persuade the reader to recognize the player's many accomplishments.</p>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n#### Now, try analyzing the expository example. \r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Spotify Year Wrapped - Music Data Cards\r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #F7F8FA; border-radius: 10px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px;\">\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 16px; \"> In this lesson, your students will use an <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1g_HJAmgWJQsveP7fTI37PYebmE4bJl6j3VIZqkMm_cI/edit?usp=sharing\" target=\"blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">activity guide</a> a to analyze the data story of three different music data cards similar to the ones below.  \r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n## ðŸ“ŒTo Do: \r\n#### Choose on